One year ago, there was a tragic act of violence at the Washington Navy Yard, where 12 people lost their lives. The President remembers and honors those who were taken from us and offers support to their families and friends. He also acknowledges the survivors who are still healing and expresses gratitude to the first responders who acted bravely. The President emphasizes the need to improve security at military bases and installations to protect those who serve and keep us safe. He calls for common-sense reforms to reduce gun violence and rejects the idea that such atrocities should become the new normal.